g.text: A services for real-time processing of streaming data
Shard: A unit of capacity in a stream. More shards = more data handling
1 Shard = 1 MB/sec of data in and 2 MB/sec out.
Data Record: A single piece of data (like logs or event) send to kinesis.
Partition Key: Used to assign records to a specific shard. (using hash function)
Producers: (your apps/devices) sends data to the stream.
Consumers: (like lambda or custom apps) read data from the stream and process it.
